state 3

    (6) strict_op -> KW_STRICT .

    KW_DIGRAPH      reduce using rule 6 (strict_op -> KW_STRICT .)


state 4

    (7) strict_op -> empty .

    KW_DIGRAPH      reduce using rule 7 (strict_op -> empty .)


state 5

    (1) program -> strict_op KW_DIGRAPH . ID LBRACE graph_body RBRACE

    ID              shift and go to state 6


state 6

    (1) program -> strict_op KW_DIGRAPH ID . LBRACE graph_body RBRACE

    LBRACE          shift and go to state 7


state 7

    (1) program -> strict_op KW_DIGRAPH ID LBRACE . graph_body RBRACE
    (2) graph_body -> . graph_body statement
    (3) graph_body -> . statement
    (4) statement -> . ID ARROW ID SEMICOLON
    (5) statement -> . ID SEMICOLON

    ID              shift and go to state 8

    graph_body                     shift and go to state 9
    statement                      shift and go to state 10

state 8

    (4) statement -> ID . ARROW ID SEMICOLON
    (5) statement -> ID . SEMICOLON

    ARROW           shift and go to state 11
    SEMICOLON       shift and go to state 12


state 9

    (1) program -> strict_op KW_DIGRAPH ID LBRACE graph_body . RBRACE
    (2) graph_body -> graph_body . statement
    (4) statement -> . ID ARROW ID SEMICOLON
    (5) statement -> . ID SEMICOLON

    RBRACE          shift and go to state 13
    ID              shift and go to state 8

    statement                      shift and go to state 14

state 10

    (3) graph_body -> statement .

    RBRACE          reduce using rule 3 (graph_body -> statement .)
    ID              reduce using rule 3 (graph_body -> statement .)


state 11

    (4) statement -> ID ARROW . ID SEMICOLON

    ID              shift and go to state 15


state 12

    (5) statement -> ID SEMICOLON .

    RBRACE          reduce using rule 5 (statement -> ID SEMICOLON .)
    ID              reduce using rule 5 (statement -> ID SEMICOLON .)


state 13

    (1) program -> strict_op KW_DIGRAPH ID LBRACE graph_body RBRACE .

    $end            reduce using rule 1 (program -> strict_op KW_DIGRAPH ID LBRACE graph_body RBRACE .)


state 14

    (2) graph_body -> graph_body statement .

    RBRACE          reduce using rule 2 (graph_body -> graph_body statement .)
